### What are you trying to do?

I'm trying to set different colors for circles on map using the options attribute but it's not working.

I'm using a function to set the circle options for each item in a observable array:
```
setCircle() {
   this.service.circles$.subscribe((res) => {
      res.forEach((x) => {
        this.circleOptions = {
          strokeColor: x.color,
          strokeOpacity: 1,
          strokeWeight: 1,
          fillColor: x.color,
          fillOpacity: 0.2
        };
      });
    });
}
```


The circles show but they all show 1 color and not the color value for each different item.

I reviewed the documentation provided: https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/reference/polygon#Circle

and it seems the only way to set the fillColor is through the options. 

Is there any way to fix this issue? How can I add different colors to each circle?

### What troubleshooting steps have you tried?

The only way to set fillColor is through options attribute.

### Reproduction

Steps to reproduce:
1. create new map 
2. add array of circles and set the options to different fillcolor as above.


### Environment

- Angular: 13.2.7
- CDK/Material: google-maps
- Browser(s): chrome
